                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2510.04290/x1.png",
                "caption": "Figure 2:Failure cases of state-of-the-art image editing models.Current state-of-the-art models often struggle to maintain physical consistency on world simulation-related editing tasks. They may hallucinate unintended objects or distort scene geometry. In contrast, our method produces edits that are faithful to the instruction and remain coherent with the scene. Prompts (from top to bottom): (1) “The left silver SUV makes a U-turn”, (2) “Pick up the spoon with the robot arm”, and (3) “Close the wooden piece by hand”.",
